From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: nix-on-z <nix-on-z@s390x>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Parquet native-reader direct-into-column paths on big-endian

Patch 0102 added LE->native byteswap to the per-element convertColumn code
path, but the Parquet V3 reader has three optimisation fast paths that
bypass convertColumn entirely and write raw PLAIN / BYTE_STREAM_SPLIT bytes
straight into IColumn's underlying storage.  On big-endian platforms those
little-endian bytes are then interpreted as native big-endian words, so
every multi-byte value comes out byte-reversed.

Concretely, a UInt64 column written by ClickHouse itself (default codec
zstd) and read back through the V3 reader returns `N << 56` instead of `N`,
because:

  Reader.cpp:readPage()
      if (!has_filter && !page.is_dictionary_encoded && whole-page &&
          page.codec != UNCOMPRESSED &&
          decoder.canReadDirectlyIntoColumn(...))
      {
          decompress(page.data, ..., span);   // LE PLAIN bytes -> IColumn
          return;                             // <-- skips convertColumn
      }

canReadDirectlyIntoColumn() returns true for PLAIN + trivial fixed-size
converter, matching virtually every fixed-width int/float column that
modern ClickHouse writes.  ClickHouse's default parquet output codec is
zstd, so `page.codec != UNCOMPRESSED` is almost always satisfied and the
fast path fires.

Two BYTE_STREAM_SPLIT direct paths have the same shape: when the converter
is trivial the split streams (stream 0 = LSB) are memcpy'd straight into
native column memory, corrupting Float32 / Float64 on BE.

Fix strategy: disable the three direct paths on big-endian targets by
forcing `direct = false` / returning false from canReadDirectlyIntoColumn
whenever the element width is > 1.  This routes BE through the already-
patched convertColumn path (fixed by 0102).  The extra memcpy+byteswap
cost only applies to s390x; LE targets are untouched at compile time.

Alternative considered: in-place byteswap after decompress() in
Reader.cpp:1965 plus similar post-passes at the BSS memcpy sites.  Not
taken because the three-line `direct = false` approach is smaller, leaves
the fully-validated convertColumn path in charge of LE decoding, and has
no risk of missing a byte width.

Observable failures resolved (all are "result differs" tests that write +
read fixed-width Parquet through v3):
  - 03727_prewhere_intermediate_columns    (UInt64 literal `N << 56` symptom)
  - 03408_parquet_row_group_profile_events (empty result)
  - assorted 02700+ parquet v3 tests producing byte-reversed sums/values
    on s390x.

No behaviour change on x86_64 (std::endian::native != std::endian::big
branch is dead at compile time).
---
--- a/src/Processors/Formats/Impl/Parquet/Decoding.cpp
+++ b/src/Processors/Formats/Impl/Parquet/Decoding.cpp
@@ -924,6 +924,13 @@
             return;
         }
         bool direct = converter->isTrivial();
+        /// BYTE_STREAM_SPLIT stores stream 0 = LSB (little-endian).  The direct
+        /// fast path memcpy's the de-interleaved bytes straight into the column's
+        /// native storage, which byte-reverses every Float32 / Float64 on BE.
+        /// Fall back to converter->convertColumn() (byteswap aware via patch 0102).
+        if constexpr (std::endian::native == std::endian::big)
+            if (converter->input_size > 1)
+                direct = false;
         temp_buffer.resize(num_values * num_streams);
         char * to = temp_buffer.data();
         requireRemainingBytes(num_values);
@@ -955,6 +962,10 @@
     void decodeNoFilter(size_t num_values, IColumn & col, size_t num_streams)
     {
         bool direct = converter->isTrivial();
+        /// See decodeWithFilter above: BSS direct path corrupts multi-byte
+        /// values on big-endian.  Route BE through convertColumn instead.
+        if constexpr (std::endian::native == std::endian::big)
+            direct = false;
         char * to = nullptr;
         if (direct)
         {
@@ -1009,6 +1020,15 @@

 bool PageDecoderInfo::canReadDirectlyIntoColumn(parq::Encoding::type encoding, size_t num_values, IColumn & col, std::span<char> & out) const
 {
+    /// On big-endian platforms the caller (Reader::readPage) decompresses the
+    /// PLAIN-encoded page directly into IColumn memory, skipping the per-element
+    /// LE->native byteswap that patch 0102 added in convertColumn.  Disable the
+    /// optimisation for multi-byte element widths so BE falls back to the
+    /// convertColumn code path.  Single-byte columns (e.g. UInt8) are unaffected
+    /// by byte order so the fast path remains available.
+    if constexpr (std::endian::native == std::endian::big)
+        if (fixed_size_converter && fixed_size_converter->input_size > 1)
+            return false;
     if (encoding == parq::Encoding::PLAIN && fixed_size_converter && physical_type != parq::Type::BOOLEAN && fixed_size_converter->isTrivial())
     {
         chassert(col.sizeOfValueIfFixed() == fixed_size_converter->input_size);
